{"TopicId":155014,"ForumId":34,"TopicTitle":"[1.4.x] BDArmory Continued v1.2.2.2 [8/8/2018] \u002B Vessel Mover, Camera Tools, BDMk22, Destruction Effects, Burn Together","CreatedByName":"DoctorDavinci","CreatedById":150019,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-14T23:16:30Z","PageNum":22,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Gorbi","CreatedById":173971,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-05T00:18:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223079412\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022155014\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221496524812\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002299498\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Inter\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 6/3/2017 at 5:20 PM, Inter said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(snip)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m pretty sure that the Physics Range Extender mod has to be used to be able to change the physics range (I remember reading this either in the readme or documentation pages somewhere). With PRE installed and configured, everything seems to work well.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"WhiteWeasel","CreatedById":59171,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-05T09:00:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n[Ver 0.2.1.1] Does anyone else get a micro stuttering issue? It seems like whenever the AI does a recalculation (like pitching up to maintain min altitude) there is a tiny, split second pause.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SpaceEnthusiast23","CreatedById":176928,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-06T02:06:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI am wondering if there is a mod or something that can make your plane stealth, so that you cannot be detects on enemy radar from BDarmory. I have built a fighter that looks stealthy to me, using quiztechaeropack, BDarmory, and stock. I want to use stealth capability when attacking someone. Any suggestions will be appreciated.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"jrodriguez","CreatedById":130617,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-06T05:11:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223081882\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022155014\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221496714799\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022176928\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022SpaceEnthusiast23\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, SpaceEnthusiast23 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI am wondering if there is a mod or something that can make your plane stealth, so that you cannot be detects on enemy radar from BDarmory. I have built a fighter that looks stealthy to me, using quiztechaeropack, BDarmory, and stock. I want to use stealth capability when attacking someone. Any suggestions will be appreciated.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI know someone opened a feature request some time ago.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/PapaJoesSoup/BDArmory/issues/43\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://github.com/PapaJoesSoup/BDArmory/issues/43\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut so far I\u0027m not aware of any mods providing this.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AkaiAndromedus","CreatedById":141213,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-06T06:43:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m having a bootup issue involving BDArmory Continued, I\u0027ve narrowed it down to BDAc through initial troubleshooting.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBelow is the Output.log.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://drive.google.com/open?id=0B7EJk6Q2W8tqZ2dBUGpzR0RCRE0\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://drive.google.com/open?id=0B7EJk6Q2W8tqZ2dBUGpzR0RCRE0\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAny help would gladly be appreciated, from my experience BDArmory Continued is a good mod.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"TheDog","CreatedById":137239,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-06T07:34:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223082065\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022155014\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221496731416\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022141213\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022AkaiAndromedus\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n47 minutes ago, AkaiAndromedus said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBelow is the Output.log.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022#\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/a\u003E \u003Cspan\u003EHide contents\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://drive.google.com/open?id=0B7EJk6Q2W8tqZ2dBUGpzR0RCRE0\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://drive.google.com/open?id=0B7EJk6Q2W8tqZ2dBUGpzR0RCRE0\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou are using an old version, please download the current release from GitHub (v.0.2.1.1). Only that can work with KSP 1.3.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SpaceEnthusiast23","CreatedById":176928,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-06T11:20:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223082013\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022155014\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221496725892\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022130617\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022jrodriguez\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 hours ago, jrodriguez said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI know someone opened a feature request some time ago.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/PapaJoesSoup/BDArmory/issues/43\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://github.com/PapaJoesSoup/BDArmory/issues/43\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut so far I\u0027m not aware of any mods providing this.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOk. Thanks anyway.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"njmksr","CreatedById":114236,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-06T17:29:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJust a question, is the rotary bomb rack broken? I saw that in one of the patch notes and I was wondering if it was fixed yet.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SpannerMonkey(smce)","CreatedById":50907,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-06T17:32:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223082590\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022155014\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221496770148\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022114236\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022njmksr\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, njmksr said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJust a question, is the rotary bomb rack broken? I saw that in one of the patch notes and I was wondering if it was fixed yet.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi, long time no see, AFAIK the rotary rack issue has been dealt with and was tracked down to the edge highlighting, (orrible green glow on parts) Should there still be an issue\u00A0 disabling edge highlighting does/did fix it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"njmksr","CreatedById":114236,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-06T17:35:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223082594\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022155014\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221496770328\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002250907\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022SpannerMonkey(smce)\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, SpannerMonkey(smce) said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi, long time no see, AFAIK the rotary rack issue has been dealt with and was tracked down to the edge highlighting, (orrible green glow on parts) Should there still be an issue\u00A0 disabling edge highlighting does/did fix it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSweet. I\u0027ve been working on some awesome new fighters and the procedural missiles looked great, as I\u0027m using Red vs. Blue\u0027s internal weapons bays, and the small bay doesn\u0027t fit that much, so space maximization is necessary.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022R2w6zyq.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/R2w6zyq.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"jrodriguez","CreatedById":130617,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-06T17:40:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223082599\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022155014\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221496770501\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022114236\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022njmksr\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 minutes ago, njmksr said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSweet. I\u0027ve been working on some awesome new fighters and the procedural missiles looked great, as I\u0027m using Red vs. Blue\u0027s internal weapons bays, and the small bay doesn\u0027t fit that much, so space maximization is necessary.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/R2w6zyq.png\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022R2w6zyq.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/R2w6zyq.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWow that looks great!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHowever there are some limitations with the procedural missiles. The bomb rack is not supported yet for example.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"njmksr","CreatedById":114236,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-06T17:48:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223082605\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022155014\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221496770815\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022130617\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022jrodriguez\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 minutes ago, jrodriguez said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWow that looks great!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHowever there are some limitations with the procedural missiles. The bomb rack is not supported yet for example.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks! That\u0027s alright, I can live with it. It looks like a great update, and it looks like it\u0027s going to be awesome with future updates.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"jrodriguez","CreatedById":130617,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-06T17:51:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223082620\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022155014\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221496771294\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022114236\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022njmksr\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, njmksr said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks! That\u0027s alright, I can live with it. It looks like a great update, and it looks like it\u0027s going to be awesome with future updates.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m glad you liked it!\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Toonu","CreatedById":18557,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-06T19:36:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223082605\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022155014\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221496770815\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022130617\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022jrodriguez\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, jrodriguez said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWow that looks great!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHowever there are some limitations with the procedural missiles. The bomb rack is not supported yet for example.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve made medium Red \u00A0vs Blue bays... Look into their forum post \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:wink:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u00A0It fits 4x GBU bombs or one AMRAAM...\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut now, question for BDA team. The\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0homingType = AGM\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0targetingType = radar\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0activeRadarRange = 6000\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0maxOffBoresight = 50\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0lockedSensorFOV = 5\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOffBoresight is in degrees in front of rocket, right? And the SensorFOV is? Also what RadarLOAL is?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOk, \u002B what is AAMPURE, AGMballistic and AAMlead or STS guidance modes?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-06-06T20:16:35Z\u0022 title=\u002206/06/2017 08:16  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EJune 6, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Toonu\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"njmksr","CreatedById":114236,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-06T19:39:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223082764\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022155014\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221496777779\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002218557\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Toonu\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, Toonu said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve made medium Red \u00A0vs Blue bays... Look into their forum post \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:wink:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u00A0It fits 4x GBU bombs or one AMRAAM...\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNah, if you use a double ejector rack you can cram two AMRAAMs in one side.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSource:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u00229bnug42.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/9bnug42.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"WhiteWeasel","CreatedById":59171,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-06T20:24:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCurious, is there a way for the AI to handle directional turrets? For example my fighter has forward facing M230\u0027s with low limits to simulate a gimballed gun, and the same idea for two rear facing 50 cal turrets. However the AI keeps defaulting to the .50 cal turrets even though the M230\u0027s are clearly in line of sight of the target and the 50\u0027s are not.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Toonu","CreatedById":18557,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-06T20:33:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223082840\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022155014\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221496780693\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002259171\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022WhiteWeasel\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 minutes ago, WhiteWeasel said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCurious, is there a way for the AI to handle directional turrets? For example my fighter has forward facing M230\u0027s with low limits to simulate a gimballed gun, and the same idea for two rear facing 50 cal turrets. However the AI keeps defaulting to the .50 cal turrets even though the M230\u0027s are clearly in line of sight of the target and the 50\u0027s are not.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSame problem here, but with ship. Its targetting incomming missiles with heavy guns instead of defence laser system integrated into ship...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGuard mode should differ it, but it would be hard to code I think...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SpannerMonkey(smce)","CreatedById":50907,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-06T20:35:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223082840\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022155014\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221496780693\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002259171\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022WhiteWeasel\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 minutes ago, WhiteWeasel said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCurious, is there a way for the AI to handle directional turrets? For example my fighter has forward facing M230\u0027s with low limits to simulate a gimballed gun, and the same idea for two rear facing 50 cal turrets. However the AI keeps defaulting to the .50 cal turrets even though the M230\u0027s are clearly in line of sight of the target and the 50\u0027s are not.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223082850\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022155014\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221496781233\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002218557\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Toonu\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, Toonu said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSame problem here, but with ship. Its targetting incomming missiles with heavy guns instead of defence laser system integrated into ship...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGuard mode should differ it, but it would be hard to code I think...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt is being worked on.\u00A0 It irritates us also.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Toonu","CreatedById":18557,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-07T06:13:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223082853\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022155014\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221496781301\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002250907\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022SpannerMonkey(smce)\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 hours ago, SpannerMonkey(smce) said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt is being worked on.\u00A0 It irritates us also.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt wasn\u0027t meant ironicaly. Not at all. I meant it that way I appreciate your work even if its not working yet. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223082013\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022155014\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221496725892\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022130617\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022jrodriguez\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 6. 6. 2017 at 7:11 AM, jrodriguez said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI know someone opened a feature request some time ago.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/PapaJoesSoup/BDArmory/issues/43\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://github.com/PapaJoesSoup/BDArmory/issues/43\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut so far I\u0027m not aware of any mods providing this.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah, I also opened one with use of \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Ferram Aerospace Research (mod)\u0022\u003EFAR\u003C/abbr\u003E voxels to calculate stealth. But it will be even harder than other ways featuring it I guess. It was at time of Bahamuto, so looong ago \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-06-07T06:17:40Z\u0022 title=\u002206/07/2017 06:17  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EJune 7, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Toonu\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"gomker","CreatedById":141269,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-07T17:52:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223082599\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022155014\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221496770501\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022114236\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022njmksr\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 6/6/2017 at 0:35 PM, njmksr said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve been working on some awesome new fighters\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNice looking planes - you ever post your stuff to\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://kerbalx.com/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://kerbalx.com/\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"WhiteWeasel","CreatedById":59171,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-08T02:20:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223082599\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022155014\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221496770501\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022114236\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022njmksr\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 6/6/2017 at 0:35 PM, njmksr said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSweet. I\u0027ve been working on some awesome new fighters...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAre those the B9 Aerospace engines? I thought that mod wasn\u0027t updated for 1.3 yet?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Brainpop14","CreatedById":149442,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-08T14:02:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs there a download link for this?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SpannerMonkey(smce)","CreatedById":50907,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-08T14:08:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223084807\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022155014\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221496930554\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022149442\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Brainpop14\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 minutes ago, Brainpop14 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs there a download link for this?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/PapaJoesSoup/BDArmory/releases/download/v0.2.1.1/BDArmory.0.2.1.1_05282017.zip\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://github.com/PapaJoesSoup/BDArmory/releases/download/v0.2.1.1/BDArmory.0.2.1.1_05282017.zip\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Guest","CreatedById":-1,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-08T22:53:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223084421\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022155014\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221496888442\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002259171\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022WhiteWeasel\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n20 hours ago, WhiteWeasel said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAre those the B9 Aerospace engines? I thought that mod wasn\u0027t updated for 1.3 yet?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSome people still use 1.2.2\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"gomker","CreatedById":141269,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-09T00:24:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223082764\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022155014\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221496777779\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002218557\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Toonu\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 6/6/2017 at 2:36 PM, Toonu said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut now, question for BDA team. The\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0homingType = AGM\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0targetingType = radar\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0activeRadarRange = 6000\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0maxOffBoresight = 50\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0lockedSensorFOV = 5\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOffBoresight is in degrees in front of rocket, right? And the SensorFOV is? Also what RadarLOAL is?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOk, \u002B what is AAMPURE, AGMballistic and AAMlead or STS guidance modes?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGoing to answer this as best I can - most of this code is from original source with some updates\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\nHoming Types\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\nAAMPURE - is in there but not implemented - Perhaps to differentiate from Ground based Anti-Air and Air launched or a legacy targeting mode left in for compatibility\u00A0\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nAAMLead - Guidance Type \u0022aam\u0022 and \u0022aamlead\u0022 both map to AAMLead in code - Missiles will lead their targets which is essential to hitting moving targets - again I think this was an evolution in targeting code by Baha\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nAGMBallistic - Ballistic targeting mode, was not used much until we tested recently. Ground to Ground rockets will have a Ballistic arc trajectory\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nSTS - Defined but not implemented\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nSensorFOV - Not implemented yet, there is a \u0022lockedSensorFOV\u0022 which is set to 2.5 right now, its used in scanning and Radar targeting calculations\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nRadarLOAL - not completely sure , from the code looks like its used in Radar targeting calculations, this is one of the areas myself and \u003Cspan\u003E@thedog are looking into\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003EOffBoreSight - yes - field of view for weapon\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n"}]}